    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wooden or metal fences acting as portable barriers, particularly in animal husbandry and otherwise in fields. Examples include fences made of oaken laths nailed onto supports, and fences made of a frame with horizontal bars interwoven or wattled with withes of hazel or willow.</Note_Text>
